The paper deals with the complexity of controlling the outcome of weighted elections, which is a topic in computational social choice. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses scoring rules, which are a common tool in machine learning and decision-making, indicating cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category.
